  "prompt": "What does \"dying from exposure\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Dying from exposure\" refers to the loss of life due to prolonged exposure to harsh environmental conditions, particularly cold or extreme weather. This can occur when a person is unable to maintain their body temperature, leading to hypothermia, or if they experience severe dehydration or other related health issues. The term can also apply to exposure to extreme heat, which can lead to heat exhaustion or heatstroke. In general, it highlights the dangers associated with being unprotected in severe weather conditions.",
